verbose_text: The monocytic myeloid lineage of BM cells under GM-CSF stimulation can further differentiate into mo/mPhi and moDCs, the latter being distinguished from the former by expression of higher levels of MHC class II but relatively lower expression of CD11b, defined as CD11c + MHCII interm CD11b hi and CD11c + MHCII hi CD11b interm respectively.
